					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh I see. It's my fault, I'm kinda sleepy (nearly 5AM now) and probably read the post too quickly. Sorry about that.
<br />
<br />My opinion on that is that if the input must be handled differently in different program sections, everything else probably will be different too, so these sections are basically different sets of main loops.
<br />
<br />I handle those in my programs as "program modules". They all set themselves up and eventually enter their main loops. Each of them is free to select which NMI routine to use and whatever else they'd like. Switching to a new module is just a matter of jumping to its reset address, and that's how the program jumps from module to module.</div>

